review:
I bought this tablet with the express purpose for watching my weekly shows and newer movies. Up to now it's been my cellphone and the S5 screen was just too small. I wasn't expecting a whole lot for the very reasonable pricing. I was very surprised at how well its serving it's purpose. At first I thought the touch screen seemed plastic looking with some haze and didn't like how easily I could put micro fine scratches made by my finger.  I was happy to find out the tablet came with a screen protector which is very convenient.

After using the tablet daily for a month, here are my observations;
The sound is so low, I cannot have any background noise even with headphones on. Battery life is impressive lasting longer than my laptop. The movie resolution is often times so noticeable its annoying and find myself tipping the tablet to see better. What I thought was a factory included screen protector turns out to be the screen itself. I do need to remind myself that I payed less than $70 for the tablet and that puts it into perspective for me. I am considering a tablet with better resolution perhaps for a Christmas present to myself. Shop around and do some homework so you won't take a few steps backwards like I did.
